upper bound on the corresponding actual Riemann zero ordinate. Using
ceilings (rather than the exact values) makes `1 / (M² + γ²)` a
provable rational lower bound on `1 / (M² + γ_actual²)`. -/
noncomputable def zeros25ceil : List ℝ :=
  [15, 22, 26, 31, 33,
