-- §CCLXXIX. Parameterized low residual explicit bound at `(T, γ₁, D)`
-- =====================================================================
-- The §CCLXXVII pair hardcoded `(T, γ₁, D) := (2π, 14, 1/2)`, but the
-- numerical audit shows this is infeasible at the worst point
-- `(x, y) = (0, 4)`: residual bound ≈ 0.77 vs model lower bound ≈ 0.20.
-- This section parameterizes the low explicit bound and the
-- arithmetic obligation over `(T, γ₁, D)` so a feasible combination
-- can be plugged in (current numerical candidate: `(10, 14, 2/5)`,
-- worst-point margin ≈ 3.6×10⁻⁴; safer fallback: `(11, 14, 1/2)`,
-- worst-point margin ≈ 9.7×10⁻³).
--
-- Adds:
--   lowResidualExplicitBoundAt                          — parameterized closed form
--   lowResidualExplicitBound_eq_At                      — specialization rfl
--   XiLowResidualExplicitDataAt                         — residual ≤ explicit bound
--   LowMarginDominatesExplicitBoundAt                   — explicit bound ≤ model margin
--   LowExplicitArithmeticBoundAt                        — pure arithmetic obligation
--   XiLowResidualMargin_of_explicitAt_and_marginAt      — bridge to XiLowResidualMargin
--   LowMarginDominatesExplicitBoundAt_twoPi_of_arithAt  — _of_arith reduction
--   XiPullbackAntiHerglotzTarget_of_twoPiModel_lowExplicitAt
