--   `|deriv side| ≤ 9yD/T² − 9yD/γ²`,
--   `|boundary| + |deriv side| ≤ closedFormFirstZeroErrorBound y T γ D`.
-- The remaining xi-side step is identifying the residual with (or
-- dominating it by) these finite IBP pieces:
--   `|Im(xiResidualError honestZeroDensityModelTwoPi z)|
--     ≤ |lowFirstZeroBoundaryTerm ... 11| + |lowFirstZeroDerivativeSide ... 11 14|`.
--
-- This section names that identification as `XiLowResidualFiniteIBPDomination`
-- (the substantive xi explicit-formula step), names the supporting
-- `S = -N₀` identity as `FirstZeroGapForDzero`, and proves the mechanical
-- closure that turns these two Props (plus integrability of `|S·k'|` on
-- `[11, 14]`) into the §CCLXXXIII `XiResidualLowIBPRepresentationAt`.
--
-- Adds:
--   XiLowResidualFiniteIBPDomination                      — residual ≤ |boundary| + |deriv|
--   FirstZeroGapForDzero                                  — S = -N₀ on first-zero gap
--   finiteFluctuation_abs_le_half_on_11_14                — |S| ≤ 1/2 on [11, 14]
--   XiResidualLowIBPRepresentationAt_11_14_half_of_finiteIBP
--                                                         — mechanical closure
