-- =====================================================================
-- §CCLXXXVII's `FirstZeroGapForDzero_of_startsAfter_at_root` introduced
-- the ugly `hN0_T0 : smoothZeroCountingN0 T0 = 0` hypothesis to match
-- the §CCLXXXV `Hgap` shape `S(T0, u) = -N₀(u)`. The structurally
-- correct identity under `DzeroStartsAfter` is
--   `S(T0, u) = N₀(T0) − N₀(u)`.
-- This section lands the adjusted Prop and a refactored AwayFromZeros
-- closure that consumes a direct numerical bound `HSbound` instead of
-- the artificial root-form `Hgap`.
--
-- The basepoint-adjustment makes the actual numerical content explicit:
-- inhabiting `HSbound` at `D = 1/2` requires `T0` chosen so that
-- `|N₀(T0) − N₀(u)| ≤ 1/2` uniformly on `[11, 14]` — a clean
-- numerical condition with no hidden irrational-root constraint. Note
-- that `T0 = 2π` gives `|S| ≤ 5/8` (since `N₀(2π) = −1/8`), not `1/2`;
-- the natural choice `T0 = 10` gives `|S| ≤ N₀(14) − N₀(10) ≈ 0.409`,
-- which is `≤ 1/2` but requires proving `N₀(10) ≥ −0.068`.
--
-- Adds:
--   FirstZeroGapForDzeroAdjusted                          — `S = N₀(T0) − N₀(u)` shape
--   FirstZeroGapForDzeroAdjusted_of_startsAfter           — clean inhabitant
