/-- 📦 **`FirstZeroGapForDzeroAdjusted Dzero T0 γ`** — structurally
correct first-zero gap identity: on `[2π, γ]`,
`finiteFluctuationPrimitive Dzero T0 u = N₀(T0) − N₀(u)`. No hidden
`N₀(T0) = 0` constraint. -/
structure FirstZeroGapForDzeroAdjusted
    (Dzero : Phase1IBP.OrderedFluctuationMeasureData) (T0 γ : ℝ) : Prop where
  fluct_eq_N0_diff :
    ∀ u : ℝ, 2 * Real.pi ≤ u → u ≤ γ →
      Phase1IBP.finiteFluctuationPrimitive Dzero T0 u
        = smoothZeroCountingN0 T0 - smoothZeroCountingN0 u

/-- 🌟🌟 **PROVED — `FirstZeroGapForDzeroAdjusted` from `DzeroStartsAfter`**
without any `N₀(T0) = 0` requirement. Direct wrap of
